<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-5779] Static type checking - Color.red recognized as int</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-5779</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;import groovy.transform.TypeChecked;&lt;br/&gt;
import java.awt.Color;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;class ColorTest&lt;br/&gt;
{&lt;br/&gt;
    @TypeChecked&lt;br/&gt;
    static main(args)&lt;/p&gt;
    {
        Color black = Color.black; // ok
        Color red = Color.red;       // Groovy:[Static type checking] - Cannot assign value of type int to variable of type java.awt.Color
    }
&lt;p&gt;}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This occurs only with colors: &apos;red&apos;, &apos;blue&apos; and &apos;green&apos;. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Groovy-Eclipse plugin Version: 2.7.2.xx-20121031-1500-e42&lt;br/&gt;
Groovy compiler level: 2.0 </environment>
