                            <comment id="14473387" author="aalmiray" created="Fri, 2 Nov 2012 08:02:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Further info: this is a problem of static scope vs instance scope. The type checker attempts to resolve getRed() as an static property, which of course shouldn&apos;t do. The Color class has lowercase and uppercase constants for some colors, such as red, green and blue (uppercase versions are recommended, lowercase versions are there for compatibility with Java 1.0 (yay backward compatibility and all the cruft it brings!)).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
